(384, 'anaskeuazo', '\\~anaskeuazw\\~ anaskeuazo', '\\@an-ask-yoo-ad''-zo\\@', 'from \\\\303\\\\ (in the sense of reversal) and a derivative of \\\\4632\\\\', '', 'v', 'subvert 1', 1, ' 1) to pack up baggage in order to carry it away to another place\r\n    1a) to move one''s furniture (when setting out for some other place)\r\n 2) of an enemy\r\n    2a) dismantling, plundering\r\n 3) of a place\r\n    3a) to overthrow, ravage destroy towns lands etc.\r\n 4) to turn away violently from a right state, to unsettle, subvert\r\n'),
