(714, 'arkeo', '\\~arkew\\~ arkeo', '\\@ar-keh''-o\\@', 'apparently a primary word [but probably akin to \\\\142\\\\ through the idea of raising a barrier]', 'TDNT - 1:464,78', 'v', 'be content 3, be sufficient 2, be enough 1, suffice 1, content 1', 8, ' 1) to be possessed of unfailing strength\r\n    1a) to be strong, to suffice, to be enough\r\n        1a1) to defend, ward off\r\n    1b) to be satisfied, to be contented\r\n'),
