(1557, 'ekdikesis', '\\~ekdikhsiv\\~ ekdikesis', '\\@ek-dik''-ay-sis\\@', 'from \\\\1556\\\\', 'TDNT - 2:445,215', 'n f', 'vengeance 4, avenge + \\\\4060\\\\ 3, revenge 1, punishment 1', 9, ' 1) a revenging, vengeance, punishment\r\n ++++\r\n In \\\\#2Co 7:11\\\\ -- meeting out of justice; doing justice to all\r\n parties. See \\\\#Lu 18:3, 21:22\\\\. The word also has the sense of\r\n acquittal and carries the sense of vindication. (Vincent III, p. 329)\r\n'),
