(2708, 'katacheo', '\\~katacew\\~ katacheo', '\\@kat-akh-eh''-o\\@', 'from \\\\2596\\\\ and cheo (to pour)', '', 'v', 'pour 2', 2, ' 1) to pour down upon\r\n 2) pour over, pour upon\r\n'),
(2709, 'katachthonios', '\\~katacyoniov\\~ katachthonios', '\\@kat-akh-thon''-ee-os\\@', 'from \\\\2596\\\\ and chthon (the ground)', 'TDNT - 3:633,421', 'adj', 'under the earth 1', 1, ' 1) subterranean\r\n    1a) refers to those who dwell in the world below, departed souls\r\n'),
(2710, 'katachraomai', '\\~katacraomai\\~ katachraomai', '\\@kat-akh-rah''-om-ahee\\@', 'from \\\\2596\\\\ and \\\\5530\\\\', '', 'v', 'abuse 2', 2, ' 1) to use much or excessively or ill\r\n 2) to use up, consume by use\r\n 3) to use fully\r\n'),
(2711, 'katapsucho', '\\~kataqucw\\~ katapsucho', '\\@kat-ap-soo''-kho\\@', 'from \\\\2596\\\\ and \\\\5594\\\\', '', 'v', 'cool 1', 1, ' 1) to cool off, make cool\r\n'),
(2712, 'kateidolos', '\\~kateidwlov\\~ kateidolos', '\\@kat-i''-do-los\\@', 'from \\\\2596\\\\ (intensive) and \\\\1497\\\\', 'TDNT - 2:379,202', 'adj', 'wholly give to idolatry 1', 1, ' 1) full of idols\r\n'),
(2713, 'katenanti', '\\~katenanti\\~ katenanti', '\\@kat-en''-an-tee\\@', 'from \\\\2596\\\\ and \\\\1725\\\\', '', 'adv', 'over against 4, before 1', 5, ' 1) over against, opposite before\r\n 2) metaph. before one i.e. he being judge\r\n'),
(2714, 'katenopion', '\\~katenwpion\\~ katenopion', '\\@kat-en-o''-pee-on\\@', 'from \\\\2596\\\\ and \\\\1799\\\\', '', 'adv', 'before 2, in sight of 1, in (one''s) sight 1, before the presence of 1', 5, ' 1) over against, before the face of, before the presence of, in\r\n    the sight of, before\r\n    1a) referring to places\r\n    1b) metaph.\r\n        1b1) having one as it were before the eyes, before one as witness\r\n        1b2) before God as judge\r\n'),
(2715, 'katexousiazo', '\\~katexousiazw\\~ katexousiazo', '\\@kat-ex-oo-see-ad''-zo\\@', 'from \\\\2596\\\\ and \\\\1850\\\\', 'TDNT - 2:575,238', 'v', 'exercise authority upon 2', 2, ' 1) to exercise authority, wield power\r\n'),
(2716, 'katergazomai', '\\~katergazomai\\~ katergazomai', '\\@kat-er-gad''-zom-ahee\\@', 'from \\\\2596\\\\ and \\\\2038\\\\', 'TDNT - 3:634,421', 'v', 'work 15, do 5, do deed 1, to perform 1, cause 1, work out 1', 24, ' 1) to perform, accomplish, achieve\r\n 2) to work out i.e. to do that from which something results\r\n    2a) of things: bring about, result in\r\n 3) to fashion i.e. render one fit for a thing\r\n'),
(2717, '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 0, '\r\n 2717 Not Used\r\n'),
(2718, 'katerchomai', '\\~katercomai\\~ katerchomai', '\\@kat-er''-khom-ahee\\@', 'from \\\\2596\\\\ and \\\\2064\\\\ (including its alternate)', '', 'v', 'come down 5, come 3, go down 2, depart 1, descend 1, land 1', 13, ' 1) to come down, go down\r\n    1a) of one who goes from a higher to a lower locality\r\n    1b) of those who come to a place by a ship\r\n'),
(2719, 'katesthio', '\\~katesyiw\\~ katesthio or \\~katafagw\\~ kataphago', '\\@kat-es-thee''-o\\@ \\@kat-aph-ag''-o\\@', 'from \\\\2596\\\\ and \\\\2068\\\\ (including its alternate)', '', 'v', 'devour 10, eat up 3, devour up 2', 15, ' 1) to consume by eating, to eat up, devour\r\n    1a) of birds\r\n    1b) of a dragon\r\n    1c) of a man eating up the little book\r\n 2) metaph.\r\n    2a) to devour i.e. squander, waste: substance\r\n    2b) to devour i.e. forcibly appropriate: widows'' property\r\n    2c) to strip one of his goods\r\n        1c1) to ruin (by the infliction of injuries)\r\n    2d) by fire, to devour i.e. to utterly consume, destroy\r\n    2e) of the consumption of the strength of body and mind by\r\n        strong emotions\r\n'),
(2720, 'kateuthuno', '\\~kateuyunw\\~ kateuthuno', '\\@kat-yoo-thoo''-no\\@', 'from \\\\2596\\\\ and \\\\2116\\\\', '', 'v', 'direct 2, guide 1', 3, ' 1) to make straight, guide, direct\r\n    1a) of the removal of the hindrances to coming to one\r\n'),
(2721, 'katephistemi', '\\~katefisthmi\\~ katephistemi', '\\@kat-ef-is''-tay-mee\\@', 'from \\\\2596\\\\ and \\\\2186\\\\', '', 'v', 'make insurrection against 1', 1, ' 1) to set up against\r\n'),
(2722, 'katecho', '\\~katecw\\~ katecho', '\\@kat-ekh''-o\\@', 'from \\\\2596\\\\ and \\\\2192\\\\', 'TDNT - 2:829,286', 'v', 'hold 3, hold fast 3, keep 2, possess 2, stay 1, take 1, have 1, make 1, misc 5', 19, ' 1) to hold back, detain, retain\r\n    1a) from going away\r\n    1b) to restrain, hinder (the course or progress of)\r\n        1b1) that which hinders, Antichrist from making his appearance\r\n        1b2) to check a ship''s headway i.e. to hold or head the ship\r\n    1c) to hold fast, keep secure, keep firm possession of\r\n 2) to get possession of, take\r\n    2b) to possess\r\n'),
(2723, 'kategoreo', '\\~kathgorew\\~ kategoreo', '\\@kat-ay-gor-eh''-o\\@', 'from \\\\2725\\\\', 'TDNT - 3:637,422', 'v', 'accuse 21, object 1', 22, ' 1) to accuse\r\n    1a) before a judge: to make an accusation\r\n    1b) of an extra-judicial accusation\r\n\r\n Sinonim   : Lihat Definisi \\\\5803\\\\\r\n'),
(2724, 'kategoria', '\\~kathgoria\\~ kategoria', '\\@kat-ay-gor-ee''-ah\\@', 'from \\\\2725\\\\', 'TDNT - 3:637,422', 'n f', 'accusation 3, accused 1', 4, ' 1) accusation, charge\r\n'),
(2725, 'kategoros', '\\~kathgorov\\~ kategoros or \\~khthgor\\~ ketegor', '\\@kat-ay''-gor-os\\@ \\@kat-ay''-gohr\\@', 'from \\\\2596\\\\ and \\\\58\\\\', 'TDNT - 3:636,422', 'n m', 'accuser 7', 7, ' 1) an accuser\r\n    1a) a name given to the devil by the rabbis\r\n'),
(2726, 'katepheia', '\\~kathfeia\\~ katepheia', '\\@kat-ay''-fi-ah\\@', 'from a compound of \\\\2596\\\\ and perhaps a derivative of the base of \\\\5316\\\\ (meaning downcast in look)', '', 'n f', 'heaviness 1', 1, ' 1) a downcast look expressive of sorrow\r\n 2) shame, dejection, gloom\r\n'),
(2727, 'katecheo', '\\~katecew\\~ katecheo', '\\@kat-ay-kheh''-o\\@', 'from \\\\2596\\\\ and \\\\2279\\\\', 'TDNT - 3:638,422', 'v', 'instruct 3, teach 3, inform 2', 8, ' 1) to sound towards, sound down upon, resound\r\n    1a) to charm with resounding sound, to fascinate\r\n 2) to teach orally, to instruct\r\n 3) to inform by word of mouth\r\n    3a) to be orally informed\r\n'),
(2728, 'katioo', '\\~katiow\\~ katioo', '\\@kat-ee-o''-o\\@', 'from \\\\2596\\\\ and a derivative of \\\\2447\\\\', 'TDNT - 3:334,*', 'v', 'canker 1', 1, ' 1) to rust over, cover with rust\r\n'),
(2729, 'katischuo', '\\~katiscuw\\~ katischuo', '\\@kat-is-khoo''-o\\@', 'from \\\\2596\\\\ and \\\\2480\\\\', 'TDNT - 3:397,378', 'v', 'prevail against 1, prevail 1', 2, ' 1) to be strong to another''s detriment, to prevail against\r\n 2) to be superior in strength\r\n 3) to overcome\r\n 4) to prevail\r\n'),
(2730, 'katoikeo', '\\~katoikew\\~ katoikeo', '\\@kat-oy-keh''-o\\@', 'from \\\\2596\\\\ and \\\\3611\\\\', 'TDNT - 5:153,674', 'v', 'dwell 42, dweller 2, inhabitor 2, inhabitant 1', 47, ' 1) to dwell, settle\r\n    1a) metaph. divine powers, influences, etc., are said to\r\n        dwell in his soul, to pervade, prompt, govern it\r\n 2) to dwell in, inhabit\r\n    2a) God is said to dwell in the temple, i.e. to be always present\r\n        for worshippers\r\n\r\n Sinonim   : Lihat Definisi \\\\5854\\\\\r\n'),
(2731, 'katoikesis', '\\~katoikhsiv\\~ katoikesis', '\\@kat-oy''-kay-sis\\@', 'from \\\\2730\\\\', '', 'n f', 'dwelling 1', 1, ' 1) dwelling, abode\r\n'),
(2732, 'katoiketerion', '\\~katoikhthrion\\~ katoiketerion', '\\@kat-oy-kay-tay''-ree-on\\@', 'from a derivative of \\\\2730\\\\', 'TDNT - 5:155,674', 'n n', 'habitation 2', 2, ' 1) an abode, a habitation\r\n'),
(2733, 'katoikia', '\\~katoikia\\~ katoikia', '\\@kat-oy-kee''-ah\\@', 'a primitive root', '', 'n f', 'habitation 1', 1, ' 1) dwelling, habitation\r\n 2) to cause to dwell, to send or bring into an abode\r\n 3) to give a dwelling to\r\n'),
(2734, 'katoptrizomai', '\\~katoptrizomai\\~ katoptrizomai', '\\@kat-op-trid''-zom-ahee\\@', 'middle voice from a compound of \\\\2596\\\\ and a derivative of \\\\3700\\\\ [cf \\\\2072\\\\]', 'TDNT - 2:696,264', 'v', 'behold as a glass 1', 1, ' 1) to show in a mirror, to make to reflect, to mirror\r\n 2) to look at one''s self in a mirror\r\n 3) to behold one''s self in a mirror\r\n'),
(2735, 'katorthoma', '\\~katorywma\\~ katorthoma', '\\@kat-or''-tho-mah\\@', 'from a compound of \\\\2596\\\\ and a derivative of \\\\3717\\\\ [cf \\\\1357\\\\]', '', 'n n', 'very worthy deed 1', 1, ' 1) a right action, a successful achievement\r\n    1a) of wholesome public measures or institutions\r\n'),
(2736, 'kato', '\\~katw\\~ kato also (cf) \\~katwterw\\~ katotero', '\\@kat''-o\\@ \\@kat-o-ter''-o\\@', '[cf \\\\2737\\\\] from \\\\2596\\\\', 'TDNT - 3:640,422', 'adv', 'down 5, beneath 3, bottom 2, under 1', 11, ' 1) down, downwards\r\n 2) below, beneath\r\n    2a) of place, below\r\n    2b) of temporal succession\r\n'),
(2737, 'katoteros', '\\~katwterov\\~ katoteros', '\\@kat-o''-ter-os\\@', 'comparative from \\\\2736\\\\', 'TDNT - 3:640,422', 'adj', 'lower 1', 1, ' 1) lower\r\n'),
(2738, 'kauma', '\\~kauma\\~ kauma', '\\@kow''-mah\\@', 'from \\\\2545\\\\', 'TDNT - 3:642,423', 'n n', 'heat 2', 2, ' 1) heat\r\n    1a) of painful and burning heat\r\n'),
(2739, 'kaumatizo', '\\~kaumatizw\\~ kaumatizo', '\\@kow-mat-id''-zo\\@', 'from \\\\2738\\\\', 'TDNT - 3:643,423', 'v', 'scorch 4', 4, ' 1) to burn with heat, to scorch\r\n 2) to be tortured with intense heat\r\n'),
(2740, 'kausis', '\\~kausiv\\~ kausis', '\\@kow''-sis\\@', 'from \\\\2545\\\\', 'TDNT - 3:643,423', 'n f', 'to be burned + \\\\1519\\\\ 1', 1, ' 1) burning, burning up\r\n'),
(2741, 'kausoo', '\\~kausow\\~ kausoo', '\\@kow-so''-o\\@', 'from \\\\2740\\\\', 'TDNT - 3:644,*', 'v', 'with fervent heat 2', 2, ' 1) to burn up, set fire to\r\n 2) to suffer with feverish burning, be parched with fever\r\n'),
(2742, 'kauson', '\\~kauswn\\~ kauson', '\\@kow''-sone\\@', 'from \\\\2741\\\\', 'TDNT - 3:644,423', 'n m', 'heat 2, burning heat 1', 3, ' 1) burning heat\r\n    1a)  of the sun\r\n 2) Eurus, a very dry hot, east wind, scorching and drying up everything\r\n'),
(2743, 'kauteriazo', '\\~kausthriazw\\~ kauteriazo', '\\@kow-tay-ree-ad''-zo\\@', 'from a derivative of \\\\2545\\\\', 'TDNT - 3:644,*', 'v', 'sear with a hot iron 1', 1, ' 1) to mark by branding, to brand, branded with their own consciences\r\n    1a) whose souls are branded with the marks of sin\r\n    1b) who carry about with them the perpetual consciousness of sin\r\n 2) seared\r\n 3) in a medical sense, to cauterise, remover by cautery\r\n'),
(2744, 'kauchaomai', '\\~kaucaomai\\~ kauchaomai', '\\@kow-khah''-om-ahee\\@', 'from some (obsolete) base akin to that of aucheo (to boast) and \\\\2172\\\\', 'TDNT - 3:645,423', 'v', 'glory 23, boast 8, rejoice 4, make boast 2, joy 1', 38, ' 1) to glory (whether with reason or without)\r\n 2) to glory on account of a thing\r\n 3) to glory in a thing\r\n'),
(2745, 'kauchema', '\\~kauchma\\~ kauchema', '\\@kow''-khay-mah\\@', 'from \\\\2744\\\\', 'TDNT - 3:645,423', 'n n', 'rejoicing 4, to glory 3, glorying 2, boasting 1, rejoice 1', 11, ' 1) that of which one glories or can glory, matter or ground of glorying\r\n 2) a glorying or boasting\r\n'),
(2746, 'kauchesis', '\\~kauchsiv\\~ kauchesis', '\\@kow''-khay-sis\\@', 'from \\\\2744\\\\', 'TDNT - 3:645,423', 'n f', 'boasting 6, rejoicing 4, glorying 1, whereof I may glory 1', 12, ' 1) the act of glorying\r\n'),
(2747, 'Kegchreai', '\\~Kegcreai\\~ Kegchreai', '\\@keng-khreh-a''-hee\\@', 'probably from kegchros (millet)', '', 'n pr loc', 'Cenchrea 3', 3, ' Cenchrea = "millet"\r\n\r\n 1) the eastern harbour of Corinth (i.e. its harbour on the Saronic\r\n    Gulf) and the emporium of its trade with the Asiatic shores of the\r\n    Mediterranean, as Lechaeum on the Corinthian Gulf connected it\r\n    with Italy and the west\r\n'),
(2748, 'Kedron', '\\~Kedpwn\\~ Kedron', '\\@ked-rone''\\@', 'of Hebrew origin \\\\06939\\\\ \\^Nwrdq\\^', '', 'n pr loc', 'Cedron 1', 1, ' Cedron or Kidron = "turbid"\r\n\r\n 1) the name of a winter torrent, rising near Jerusalem and flowing\r\n    down through a valley of Kidron, having the Mount of Olives on the\r\n    east, into the Dead Sea\r\n'),
(2749, 'keimai', '\\~keimai\\~ keimai', '\\@ki''-mahee\\@', 'middle voice of a primary verb', 'TDNT - 3:654,425', 'v', 'lie 9, be laid 6, be set 6, be appointed 1, be 1, be made 1, laid up 1, there 1', 26, ' 1) to lie\r\n    1a) of an infant\r\n    1b) of one buried\r\n    1c) of things that quietly  cover some spot\r\n        1c1) of a city situated on a hill\r\n    1d) of things put or set in any place, in ref. to which we often\r\n        use "to stand"\r\n        1d1) of vessels, of a throne, of the site of a city, of grain\r\n             and other things laid up together, of a foundation\r\n 2) metaph.\r\n    2a) to be (by God''s intent) set, i.e. destined, appointed\r\n    2b) of laws, to be made, laid down\r\n    2c) lies in the power of the evil one, i.e. is held in\r\n        subjection by the devil\r\n'),
(2750, 'keiria', '\\~keiria\\~ keiria', '\\@ki-ree''-ah\\@', 'of uncertain affinity', '', 'n f', 'graveclothes 1', 1, ' 1) a band, either for bed-girth, or for tying up a corpse after\r\n    it has been swathed in linen\r\n'),
(2751, 'keiro', '\\~keirw\\~ keiro', '\\@ki''-ro\\@', 'a primary verb', '', 'v', 'shear 3, shearer 1', 4, ' 1) to sheer: a sheep\r\n 2) to get or let be shorn\r\n 3) of shearing or cutting short the hair of the head\r\n'),
(2752, 'keleuma', '\\~keleusma\\~ keleuma', '\\@kel''-yoo-mah\\@', 'from \\\\2753\\\\', 'TDNT - 3:656,*', 'n n', 'shout 1', 1, ' 1) an order, command, spec. a stimulating cry, either that by which\r\n    animals are roused and urged on by man, as horses by charioteers,\r\n    hounds by hunters, etc., or that by which a signal is given to\r\n    men, e.g. to rowers by the master of a ship, to soldiers by a\r\n    commander (with a loud summons, a trumpet call)\r\n'),
(2753, 'keleuo', '\\~keleuw\\~ keleuo', '\\@kel-yoo''-o\\@', 'from a primary kello (to urge on)', '', 'v', 'command 24, at (one''s) command 1, give commandment 1, bid 1', 27, ' 1) to command, to order\r\n\r\n Sinonim   : Lihat Definisi \\\\5844\\\\\r\n'),
(2754, 'kenodoxia', '\\~kenodoxia\\~ kenodoxia', '\\@ken-od-ox-ee''-ah\\@', 'from \\\\2755\\\\', 'TDNT - 3:662,426', 'n f', 'vainglory 1', 1, ' 1) vain glory, groundless, self esteem, empty pride\r\n 2) a vain opinion, error\r\n'),
(2755, 'kenodoxos', '\\~kenodoxov\\~ kenodoxos', '\\@ken-od''-ox-os\\@', 'from \\\\2756\\\\ and \\\\1391\\\\', 'TDNT - 3:662,426', 'adj', 'desirous of vain glory 1', 1, ' 1) glorying without reason, conceited, vain glorious,\r\n    eager for empty glory\r\n'),
(2756, 'kenos', '\\~kenov\\~ kenos', '\\@ken-os''\\@', 'apparently a primary word', 'TDNT - 3:659,426', 'adj', 'vain 9, in vain 4, empty 4, vain things 1', 18, ' 1) empty, vain, devoid of truth\r\n    1a) of places, vessels, etc. which contain nothing\r\n    1b) of men\r\n        1b1) empty handed\r\n        1b2) without a gift\r\n    1c) metaph. destitute of spiritual wealth, of one who boasts of his\r\n        faith as a transcendent possession, yet is without the fruits\r\n        of faith\r\n    1d) metaph. of endeavours, labours, acts, which result in nothing,\r\n        vain, fruitless, without effect\r\n        1d1) vain of no purpose\r\n'),
(2757, 'kenophonia', '\\~kenofwnia\\~ kenophonia', '\\@ken-of-o-nee''-ah\\@', 'from a presumed compound of \\\\2756\\\\ and \\\\5456\\\\', '', 'n f', 'vain babblings 2', 2, ' 1) empty discussion, discussion of vain and useless matters\r\n'),
(2758, 'kenoo', '\\~kenow\\~ kenoo', '\\@ken-o''-o\\@', 'from \\\\2756\\\\', 'TDNT - 3:661,426', 'v', 'make void 2, make of none effect 1, make of no reputation 1, be in vain 1', 5, ' 1) to empty, make empty\r\n    1a) of Christ, he laid aside equality with or the form of God\r\n 2) to make void\r\n    2a) deprive of force, render vain, useless, of no effect\r\n 3) to make void\r\n    3b) cause a thing to be seen to be empty, hollow, false\r\n'),
(2759, 'kentron', '\\~kentron\\~ kentron', '\\@ken''-tron\\@', 'from kenteo (to prick)', 'TDNT - 3:663,427', 'n n', 'sting 3, prick 2', 5, ' 1) a sting, as that of bees, scorpions, locusts. Since animals\r\n    wound by their sting and even cause death, Paul attributes\r\n    death, personified as a sting, i.e. a deadly weapon\r\n 2) an iron goad, for urging on oxen, horses and other beasts of burden\r\n    2a) hence the proverb, "to kick against the goad", i.e. to offer\r\n        vain and perilous or ruinous resistance\r\n'),
(2760, 'kenturion', '\\~kenturiwn\\~ kenturion', '\\@ken-too-ree''-ohn\\@', 'of Latin origin', '', 'n m', 'centurion 3', 3, ' 1) centurion, an officer in the Roman army\r\n'),
(2761, 'kenos', '\\~kenwv\\~ kenos', '\\@ken-oce''\\@', 'from \\\\2756\\\\', '', 'adv', 'in vain 1', 1, ' 1) vainly, in vain\r\n'),
(2762, 'keraia', '\\~keraia\\~ keraia', '\\@ker-ah''-yah\\@', 'from a presumed derivative of the base of \\\\2768\\\\', '', 'n f', 'tittle 2', 2, ' 1) a little horn\r\n 2) extremity, apex, point\r\n    2a) used by grammarians of the accents and diacritical points.\r\n        Jesus used it of the little lines or projections, by which the\r\n        Hebrew letters in other respects similar differ from one\r\n        another; the meaning is, "not even the minutest part of the\r\n        law shall perish".\r\n'),
(2763, 'kerameus', '\\~kerameuv\\~ kerameus', '\\@ker-am-yooce''\\@', 'from \\\\2766\\\\', '', 'n m', 'potter 3', 3, ' 1) a potter\r\n'),
(2764, 'keramikos', '\\~keramikov\\~ keramikos', '\\@ker-am-ik-os''\\@', 'from \\\\2766\\\\', '', 'adj', 'of a potter 1', 1, ' 1) of or belonging to a potter\r\n 2) made of clay, earthen\r\n'),
(2765, 'keramion', '\\~keramion\\~ keramion', '\\@ker-am''-ee-on\\@', 'from a presumed derivative of \\\\2766\\\\', '', 'n n', 'pitcher 2', 2, ' 1) an earthen vessel, a pot, jar\r\n 2) a jug or pitcher\r\n 3) a water pitcher\r\n'),
(2766, 'keramos', '\\~keramov\\~ keramos', '\\@ker''-am-os\\@', 'probably from the base of \\\\2767\\\\ (through the idea of mixing clay and water)', '', 'n m', 'tiling 1', 1, ' 1) clay, potter''s earth\r\n 2) anything made of clay, earthen ware\r\n 3) a roofing tile\r\n    3a) the roof itself\r\n    3b) the phrase "through the roof", means through the door in the\r\n        roof to which a ladder or stairway led up from the street\r\n        (according to the Rabbis distinguish two ways of entering a\r\n        house, "the way through the door" and "the way through the\r\n        roof"\r\n\r\n Sinonim   : Lihat Definisi \\\\5858\\\\\r\n'),
(2767, 'kerannumi', '\\~kerannumi\\~ kerannumi', '\\@ker-an''-noo-mee\\@', 'a prolonged form of a more primary \\~keraw\\~ kerao \\@ker-ah''-o\\@ (which is used in certain tenses)', '', 'v', 'fill 2, pour out 1', 3, ' 1) to mix, mingle\r\n 2) to mix wine, water\r\n 3) to pour out for drinking.\r\n'),
(2768, 'keras', '\\~kerav\\~ keras', '\\@ker''-as\\@', 'from a primary kar (the hair of the head)', 'TDNT - 3:669,428', 'n n', 'horn 11', 11, ' 1) a horn\r\n    1a) of animals\r\n    1b) since animals (esp. bulls) defend themselves with their horns,\r\n        the horn with the Hebrews (and other nations) is a symbol of\r\n        strength and courage, and used as such in a variety of phrases\r\n        1b1) a mighty and valiant helper, the author of deliverance,\r\n             of the Messiah\r\n    1c) a projecting extremity in a shape like a horn, a point, apex:\r\n        as of an altar\r\n'),
(2769, 'keration', '\\~keration\\~ keration', '\\@ker-at''-ee-on\\@', 'from a presumed derivative of \\\\2768\\\\', '', 'n n', 'husk 1', 1, ' 1) a little horn\r\n 2) the name of the fruit, Ceratonia silqua or carobtree (called also\r\n    John''s Bread [from the notion that its pods, which resemble those\r\n    of the "locust", constituted the food of the Baptist]. This fruit\r\n    was shaped like a horn and has a sweet taste; it was and is used\r\n    not only for fattening swine, but as an article of food by the\r\n    lower classes.\r\n'),
(2770, 'kerdaino', '\\~kerdainw\\~ kerdaino', '\\@ker-dah''-ee-no\\@', 'from \\\\2771\\\\', 'TDNT - 3:672,428', 'v', 'gain 13, win 2, get gain 1, vr gain 1', 17, ' 1) to gain, acquire, to get gain\r\n 2) metaph.\r\n    2a) of gain arising from shunning or escaping from evil (where we\r\n        say "to spare one''s self", "be spared")\r\n    2b) to gain any one i.e. to win him over to the kingdom of God, to\r\n        gain one to faith in Christ\r\n    2c) to gain Christ''s favour and fellowship\r\n'),
(2771, 'kerdos', '\\~kerdov\\~ kerdos', '\\@ker''-dos\\@', 'of uncertain affinity', 'TDNT - 3:672,428', 'n n', 'gain 2, lucre 1', 3, ' 1) gain, advantage\r\n'),
(2772, 'kerma', '\\~kerma\\~ kerma', '\\@ker''-mah\\@', 'from \\\\2751\\\\', '', 'n n', 'money 1', 1, ' 1) small pieces of money, small coin, change, money\r\n'),
(2773, 'kermatistes', '\\~kermatisthv\\~ kermatistes', '\\@ker-mat-is-tace''\\@', 'from a derivative of \\\\2772\\\\', '', 'n m', 'changer of money 1', 1, ' 1) a money changer, money broker\r\n\r\n In the court of the Gentiles in the temple of Jerusalem were the\r\n seats of those who sold such animals for sacrifice as had been\r\n selected, examined, and approved, together with incense, oil, and\r\n other things needed in making offerings and in worship; and the\r\n magnitude of this traffic had introduced the banker''s or broker''s\r\n business.\r\n'),
(2774, 'kephalaion', '\\~kefalaion\\~ kephalaion', '\\@kef-al''-ah-yon\\@', 'from a derivative of \\\\2776\\\\', '', 'n n', 'sum 2', 2, ' 1) the chief or main point, the principal thing\r\n 2) the pecuniary sum total of a reckoning, amount\r\n    2a) the principal, capital, as distinguished from the interest\r\n    2b) a sum of money, sum\r\n'),
(2775, 'kephalaioo', '\\~kefalaiow\\~ kephalaioo', '\\@kef-al-ahee-o''-o\\@', 'from the same as \\\\2774\\\\', '', 'v', 'wound in the head 1', 1, ' 1) to bring under headings, to sum up, to summarise\r\n 2) to smite or wound in the head, to smite on the cheek\r\n'),
(2776, 'kephale', '\\~kefalh\\~ kephale', '\\@kef-al-ay''\\@', 'from the primary kapto (in the sense of seizing)', 'TDNT - 3:673,429', 'n f', 'head 76', 76, ' 1) the head, both of men and often of animals. Since the loss of the\r\n    head destroys life, this word is used in the phrases relating to\r\n    capital and extreme punishment.\r\n 2) metaph. anything  supreme, chief, prominent\r\n    2a) of persons, master lord: of a husband in relation to his wife\r\n    2b) of Christ: the Lord of the husband and of the Church\r\n    2c) of things: the corner stone\r\n'),
(2777, 'kephalis', '\\~kefaliv\\~ kephalis', '\\@kef-al-is''\\@', 'from \\\\2776\\\\', '', 'n f', 'volume 1', 1, ' 1) a little head\r\n 2) the highest part, extremity of anything\r\n    2a) as the capital of a column\r\n    2b) the tips or knobs of the wooden rod around which parchments were\r\n        rolled were called by this word, because they resembled little\r\n        heads\r\n 3) the Alexandrian writers transferred the name to the roll or volume\r\n    itself\r\n    3a) in the roll of the book\r\n'),
(2778, 'kensos', '\\~khnsov\\~ kensos', '\\@kane''-sos\\@', 'of Latin origin', '', 'n m', 'tribute 4', 4, ' 1) census (among the Romans, denoting a register and valuation of\r\n    property in accordance with which taxes were paid), in the NT the\r\n    tax or tribute levied on individuals and to be paid yearly. (our\r\n    capitation or poll tax)\r\n 2) the coin with which the tax is paid, tribute money\r\n\r\n Sinonim   : Lihat Definisi \\\\5941\\\\\r\n'),
(2779, 'kepos', '\\~khpov\\~ kepos', '\\@kay''-pos\\@', 'of uncertain affinity', '', 'n m', 'garden 5', 5, ' 1) a garden\r\n'),
(2780, 'kepouros', '\\~khpourov\\~ kepouros', '\\@kay-poo-ros''\\@', 'from \\\\2779\\\\ and ouros (a warden)', '', 'n m', 'gardener 1', 1, ' 1) a keeper of a garden, a gardener\r\n'),
(2781, 'kerion', '\\~khrion\\~ kerion', '\\@kay-ree''-on\\@', 'diminutive from keos (wax)', '', 'n n', 'honeycomb + \\\\3193\\\\ 1', 1, ' 1) honeycomb\r\n'),
(2782, 'kerugma', '\\~khrugma\\~ kerugma', '\\@kay''-roog-mah\\@', 'from \\\\2784\\\\', 'TDNT - 3:714,430', 'n n', 'preaching 8', 8, ' 1) that which is proclaimed by a herald or public crier, a\r\n    proclamation by herald\r\n 2) in the NT the message or proclamation of the heralds of God or\r\n    Christ\r\n'),
(2783, 'kerux', '\\~khrux\\~ kerux', '\\@kay''-roox\\@', 'from \\\\2784\\\\', 'TDNT - 3:683,430', 'n m', 'preacher 3', 3, ' 1) a herald or messenger vested with public authority, who conveyed\r\n    the official messages of kings, magistrates, princes, military\r\n    commanders, or who gave a public summons or demand, and performed\r\n    various other duties. In the NT God''s ambassador, and the herald\r\n    or proclaimer of the divine word.\r\n'),
(2784, 'kerusso', '\\~khrussw\\~ kerusso', '\\@kay-roos''-so\\@', 'of uncertain affinity', 'TDNT - 3:697,430', 'v', 'preach 51, publish 5, proclaim 2, preached + \\\\2258\\\\ 2, preacher 1', 61, ' 1) to be a herald, to officiate as a herald\r\n    1a) to proclaim after the manner of a herald\r\n    1b) always with the suggestion of formality, gravity and an\r\n        authority which must be listened to and obeyed\r\n 2) to publish, proclaim openly: something which has been done\r\n 3) used of the public proclamation of the gospel and matters\r\n    pertaining to it, made by John the Baptist, by Jesus, by the\r\n    apostles and other Christian teachers\r\n'),
(2785, 'ketos', '\\~khtov\\~ ketos', '\\@kay''-tos\\@', 'probably from the base of \\\\5490\\\\', '', 'n n', 'whale 1', 1, ' 1) a sea monster, whale, huge fish\r\n'),
(2786, 'Kephas', '\\~khfav\\~ Kephas', '\\@kay-fas''\\@', 'of Aramaic origin, cf \\\\03710\\\\ \\^apyk\\^', 'TDNT - 6:100,835', 'n pr m', 'Cephas 6', 6, ' Cephas = "stone"\r\n\r\n 1) another name for the apostle Peter\r\n'),
(2787, 'kibotos', '\\~kibwtov\\~ kibotos', '\\@kib-o-tos''\\@', 'of uncertain derivation', '', 'n f', 'ark 6', 6, ' 1) a wooden chest or box\r\n 2) in the NT the ark of the covenant, in the temple at Jerusalem\r\n 3) of Noah''s vessel built in the form of an ark\r\n'),
(2788, 'kithara', '\\~kiyara\\~ kithara', '\\@kith-ar''-ah\\@', 'of uncertain affinity', '', 'n f', 'harp 4', 4, ' 1) a harp to which praises of God are sung in heaven\r\n'),
(2789, 'kitharizo', '\\~kiyarizw\\~ kitharizo', '\\@kith-ar-id''-zo\\@', 'from \\\\2788\\\\', '', 'v', 'to harp 2', 2, ' 1) to play upon the harp\r\n'),
(2790, 'kitharodos', '\\~kiyarwdov\\~ kitharodos', '\\@kith-ar-o''-dos\\@', 'from \\\\2788\\\\ and a derivative of the same as \\\\5603\\\\', '', 'n m', 'harper 2', 2, ' 1) a harper, one who plays the harp and accompanies it with his voice\r\n'),
(2791, 'Kilikia', '\\~Kilikia\\~ Kilikia', '\\@kil-ik-ee''-ah\\@', 'probably of foreign origin', '', 'n pr loc', 'Cilicia 8', 8, ' Cilicia = "the land of Celix"\r\n\r\n 1) a maritime province in the southeast of Asia Minor, boarding on\r\n    Pamphylia in the west, Lycaonia and Cappadocia in the north and\r\n    Syria in the east. Its capital, Tarsus, was the birth place of Paul\r\n'),
(2792, 'kinamomon', '\\~kinnamwmon\\~ kinamomon', '\\@kin-am''-o-mon\\@', 'of foreign origin cf \\\\7076\\\\', '', 'n n', 'cinnamon 1', 1, ' 1) cinnamon was a well known aromatic substance, the rind of\r\n    "Laurus cinnamonum" called "Korunda-gauhah" in Ceylon\r\n'),
(2793, 'kinduneuo', '\\~kinduneuw\\~ kinduneuo', '\\@kin-doon-yoo''-o\\@', 'from \\\\2794\\\\', '', 'v', 'be in danger 2, be in jeopardy 1, stand in jeopardy 1', 4, ' 1) to be in jeopardy, to be in danger, to put in peril\r\n'),
(2794, 'kindunos', '\\~kindunov\\~ kindunos', '\\@kin''-doo-nos\\@', 'of uncertain derivation', '', 'n m', 'peril 9', 9, ' 1) a danger, a peril\r\n'),
(2795, 'kineo', '\\~kinew\\~ kineo', '\\@kin-eh''-o\\@', 'from kio (poetic for eimi, to go)', 'TDNT - 3:718,435', 'v', 'move 4, wag 2, remove 1, mover 1', 8, ' 1) to cause to go, i.e. to move, set in motion\r\n    1a) to be moved, move: of that motion which is evident in life\r\n    1b) to move from a place, to remove\r\n 2) metaph.\r\n    2a) to move excite\r\n    2b) a riot, disturbance\r\n    2c) to throw into commotion\r\n'),
(2796, 'kinesis', '\\~kinhsiv\\~ kinesis', '\\@kin''-ay-sis\\@', 'from \\\\2795\\\\', '', 'n f', 'moving 1', 1, ' 1) a moving, agitation\r\n'),
(2797, 'Kis', '\\~Kiv\\~ Kis', '\\@kis\\@', 'of Hebrew origin \\\\07027\\\\ \\^vyq\\^', '', 'n pr m', 'Cis 1', 1, ' Kish = "a snare"\r\n\r\n 1) the father of Saul, the first king of Israel\r\n'),
(2798, 'klados', '\\~kladov\\~ klados', '\\@klad''-os\\@', 'from \\\\2806\\\\', 'TDNT - 3:720,*', 'n m', 'branch 11', 11, ' 1) a young tender shoot, broken off for grafting\r\n 2) a branch\r\n    2a) as the Jewish patriarchs are likened to a root, so their\r\n        posterity are likened to branches\r\n'),
(2799, 'klaio', '\\~klaiw\\~ klaio', '\\@klah''-yo\\@', 'of uncertain affinity', 'TDNT - 3:722,436', 'v', 'weep 39, bewail 1', 40, ' 1) to mourn, weep, lament\r\n    1a) weeping as the sign of pain and grief for the thing signified\r\n        (i.e. for the pain and grief)\r\n    1b) of those who mourn for the dead\r\n 2) to weep for, mourn for, bewail, one\r\n\r\n Sinonim   : Lihat Definisi \\\\5804\\\\\r\n'),
(2800, 'klasis', '\\~klasiv\\~ klasis', '\\@klas''-is\\@', 'from \\\\2806\\\\', 'TDNT - 3:726,437', 'n f', 'breaking 2', 2, ' 1) a breaking\r\n'),
(2801, 'klasma', '\\~klasma\\~ klasma', '\\@klas''-mah\\@', 'from \\\\2806\\\\', 'TDNT - 3:726,437', 'n n', 'fragment 7, broken meat 2', 9, ' 1) a fragment, broken piece\r\n    1a) remnants of food\r\n'),
(2802, 'Klaude', '\\~Klauda\\~ Klaude', '\\@klow''-day\\@', 'of uncertain derivation', '', 'n pr loc', 'Clauda 1', 1, ' Clauda = "lame"\r\n\r\n 1) a small island nearly due west of Cape Malta on the south coast\r\n   of Crete, and nearly due south of Phoenice\r\n'),
(2803, 'Klaudia', '\\~Klaudia\\~ Klaudia', '\\@klow-dee''-ah\\@', 'from \\\\2804\\\\', '', 'n pr f', 'Claudia 1', 1, ' Claudia = "lame"\r\n\r\n 1) a Christian woman\r\n'),
(2804, 'Klaudios', '\\~Klaudiov\\~ Klaudios', '\\@klow''-dee-os\\@', 'of Latin origin', '', 'n pr m', 'Claudius (Caesar) 2, Claudius (Lysias) 1', 3, ' Claudius = "lame"\r\n\r\n 1) C. Caesar the name of the fourth Roman emperor, who came to power\r\n    in 41 A.D. and was poisoned by his wife Agrippina, in 54 A.D.\r\n 2) C. Lysias a tribune of the Roman cohort who rescued Paul from the\r\n    hands of the mob at Jerusalem\r\n'),
(2805, 'klauthmos', '\\~klauymov\\~ klauthmos', '\\@klowth-mos''\\@', 'from \\\\2799\\\\', 'TDNT - 3:725,436', 'n m', 'weeping 6, wailing 2, weep 1', 9, ' 1) weeping, lamentation\r\n'),
(2806, 'klao', '\\~klaw\\~ klao', '\\@klah''-o\\@', 'a primary verb', 'TDNT - 3:726,437', 'v', 'break 15', 15, ' 1) to break\r\n    1a) used in the NT of the breaking of bread or communion\r\n'),
(2807, 'kleis', '\\~kleiv\\~ kleis', '\\@klice\\@', 'from \\\\2808\\\\', 'TDNT - 3:744,439', 'n f', 'key 6', 6, ' 1) a key\r\n    1a) since the keeper of the keys has the power to open and to shut\r\n    1b) metaph. in the NT to denote power and authority of various kinds\r\n'),
(2808, 'kleio', '\\~kleiw\\~ kleio', '\\@kli''-o\\@', 'a primary verb', '', 'v', 'shut 12, shut up 4', 16, ' 1) to shut, shut up\r\n 2) metaph.\r\n    2a) to cause the heavens to withhold rain\r\n    2b) to shut up compassion so that it is like a thing inaccessible\r\n        to one, to be devoid of pity towards one\r\n    2c) to obstruct the entrance into the kingdom of heaven\r\n'),
(2809, 'klemma', '\\~klemma\\~ klemma', '\\@klem''-mah\\@', 'from \\\\2813\\\\', '', 'n n', 'theft 1', 1, ' 1) thing stolen\r\n 2) the act of theft\r\n'),
(2810, 'Kleopas', '\\~Kleopav\\~ Kleopas', '\\@kleh-op''-as\\@', 'probably contracted from Kleopatros (compound of \\\\2811\\\\ and \\\\3962\\\\)', '', 'n pr m', 'Cleopas 1', 1, ' Cleopas = "of a renowned father"\r\n\r\n 1) one of the two disciples who were going to Emmaus on the day of\r\n    the resurrection\r\n'),
(2811, 'kleos', '\\~kleov\\~ kleos', '\\@kleh''-os\\@', 'from a shorter form of \\\\2564\\\\', '', 'n n', 'glory 1', 1, ' 1) rumour, report\r\n 2) glory, praise\r\n'),
(2812, 'kleptes', '\\~klepthv\\~ kleptes', '\\@klep''-tace\\@', 'from \\\\2813\\\\', 'TDNT - 3:754,441', 'n m', 'thief 16', 16, ' 1) an embezzler, pilferer\r\n    1a) the name is transferred to false teachers, who do not care to\r\n        instruct men, but abuse their confidence for their own gain\r\n\r\n Sinonim   : Lihat Definisi \\\\5856\\\\\r\n'),
(2813, 'klepto', '\\~kleptw\\~ klepto', '\\@klep''-to\\@', 'a primary verb', 'TDNT - 3:754,441', 'v', 'steal 13', 13, ' 1) to steal\r\n    1a) to commit a theft\r\n    1b) take away by theft i.e take away by stealth\r\n'),
(2814, 'klema', '\\~klhma\\~ klema', '\\@kaly''-mah\\@', 'from \\\\2806\\\\', 'TDNT - 3:757,441', 'n n', 'branch 4', 4, ' 1) a tender and flexible branch\r\n 2) spec. the shoot or branch of a vine, a vine sprout\r\n'),
(2815, 'Klemes', '\\~Klhmhv\\~ Klemes', '\\@klay''-mace\\@', 'of Latin origin', '', 'n pr m', 'Clement 1', 1, ' Clement = "mild, merciful"\r\n\r\n 1) a companion of Paul and apparently a member of the church of\r\n    Philippi. According to tradition, he is identical with that\r\n    Clement who was bishop of Rome towards the close of the first\r\n    century.\r\n'),
(2816, 'kleronomeo', '\\~klhronomew\\~ kleronomeo', '\\@klay-ron-om-eh''-o\\@', 'from \\\\2818\\\\', 'TDNT - 3:767,442', 'v', 'inherit 15, be heir 2, obtain by inheritance 1', 18, ' 1) to receive a lot, receive by lot\r\n    1a) esp. to receive a part of an inheritance, receive as an\r\n        inheritance, obtain by right of inheritance\r\n    1b) to be an heir, to inherit\r\n 2) to receive the portion assigned to one, receive an allotted\r\n    portion, receive as one''s own or as a possession\r\n 3) to become partaker of, to obtain\r\n'),
(2817, 'kleronomia', '\\~klhronomia\\~ kleronomia', '\\@klay-ron-om-ee''-ah\\@', 'from \\\\2818\\\\', 'TDNT - 3:767,442', 'n f', 'inheritance 14', 14, ' 1) an inheritance, property received (or to be received) by inheritance\r\n 2) what is given to one as a possession\r\n    2a) the eternal blessedness of the consummated kingdom of God\r\n        which is to be expected after the visible return of Christ\r\n    2b) the share which an individual will have in that eternal\r\n        blessedness\r\n'),
(2818, 'kleronomos', '\\~klhronomov\\~ kleronomos', '\\@klay-ron-om''-os\\@', 'from \\\\2819\\\\ and the base of \\\\3551\\\\ (in its original sense of partitioning, i.e. [reflexively] getting by apportionment)', 'TDNT - 3:767,442', 'n m', 'heir 15', 15, ' 1) one who receives by lot, an heir\r\n    1a) an heir\r\n    1b) in Messianic usage, one who receives his allotted\r\n        possession by right of sonship\r\n 2) one who has acquired or obtained the portion allotted to him\r\n'),
(2819, 'kleros', '\\~klhrov\\~ kleros', '\\@klay''-ros\\@', 'probably from \\\\2806\\\\ (through the idea of using bits of wood, etc., for the purpose)', 'TDNT - 3:758,442', 'n m', 'lot 8, part 2, inheritance 2, heritage 1', 13, ' 1) an object used in casting or drawing lots, which was either a\r\n    pebble, or a potsherd, or a bit of wood\r\n    1a) the lots of several persons concerned, inscribed with their\r\n        names, were thrown together into a vase, which was then\r\n        shaken, and he whose lot fell out first upon the ground was\r\n        the one chosen\r\n 2) what is obtained by lot, allotted portion\r\n    2a) a portion of the ministry common to the apostles\r\n    2b) used of the part which one will have in eternal salvation\r\n        2b1) of salvation itself\r\n        2b2) the eternal salvation which God has assigned to the saints\r\n    2c) of persons\r\n        2c1) those whose care and oversight has been assigned to\r\n             one [allotted charge], used of Christian churches, the\r\n             administration of which falls to the lot of presbyters\r\n'),
(2820, 'kleroo', '\\~klhrow\\~ kleroo', '\\@klay-ro-o\\@', 'from \\\\2819\\\\', 'TDNT - 3:764,442', 'v', 'obtain an inheritance 1', 1, ' 1) to cast lots, determine by lot\r\n 2) to choose by lot\r\n 3) to allot, assign by lot\r\n    3a) on to another as a possession\r\n 4) in NT: to make a lot, i.e. a heritage, private possession\r\n'),
(2821, 'klesis', '\\~klhsiv\\~ klesis', '\\@klay''-sis\\@', 'from a shorter form of \\\\2564\\\\', 'TDNT - 3:491,394', 'n f', 'calling 10, vocation 1', 11, ' 1) a calling, calling to\r\n 2) a call, invitation\r\n    2a) to a feast\r\n    2b) of the divine invitation to embrace salvation of God\r\n'),
(2822, 'kletos', '\\~klhtov\\~ kletos', '\\@klay-tos''\\@', 'from the same as \\\\2821\\\\', 'TDNT - 3:494,394', 'adj', 'called 11', 11, ' 1) called, invited (to a banquet)\r\n    1a) invited (by God in the proclamation of the Gospel) to\r\n        obtain eternal salvation in the kingdom through Christ\r\n    1b) called to (the discharge of) some office\r\n        1b1) divinely selected and appointed\r\n');
INSERT INTO `greek` (`id`, `word_id`, `word`, `pron`, `origin`, `source`, `kind`, `av`, `count`, `definition`) VALUES
(2823, 'klibanos', '\\~klibanov\\~ klibanos', '\\@klib''-an-os\\@', 'of uncertain derivation', '', 'n m', 'oven 2', 2, ' 1) a clibanus, a earthen vessel for baking bread. It was broader at\r\n    the bottom than above at the orifice, and when sufficiently heated\r\n    by a fire kindled within, the dough was baked by being spread upon\r\n    the outside. [but according to others, the dough was baked by\r\n    being placed inside and the fire or coals outside, the vessel\r\n    being perforated with small holes that the heat might better\r\n    penetrate.\r\n 2) a furnace, oven\r\n'),
(2824, 'klima', '\\~klima\\~ klima', '\\@klee''-mah\\@', 'from \\\\2827\\\\', '', 'n n', 'region 2, part 1', 3, ' 1) an inclination, slope, declivity\r\n 2) the [supposed] sloping of the earth from the equator towards the\r\n    poles, a zone\r\n 3) a tract of land, a region\r\n'),
(2825, 'kline', '\\~klinh\\~ kline', '\\@klee''-nay\\@', 'from \\\\2827\\\\', '', 'n n', 'bed 9, table 1', 10, ' 1) a small bed, a couch\r\n 2) a couch to recline on at meals\r\n 3) a couch on which a sick man is carried\r\n'),
(2826, 'klinidion', '\\~klinidion\\~ klinidion', '\\@klin-id''-ee-on\\@', 'from a presumed derivative of \\\\2825\\\\', '', 'n n', 'couch 2', 2, ' 1) a small bed, a couch\r\n'),
(2827, 'klino', '\\~klinw\\~ klino', '\\@klee''-no\\@', 'a root word', '', 'v', 'lay 2, bow 1, bow down 1, be far spent 1, turn to fight 1, wear away 1', 7, ' 1) transitively\r\n    1a) to incline, bow\r\n    1b) to cause to fall back\r\n    1c) to recline\r\n        1c1) in a place for repose\r\n 2) intransitively\r\n    2a) to incline one''s self\r\n        2a1) of the declining of the day\r\n'),
(2828, 'klisia', '\\~klisia\\~ klisia', '\\@klee-see''-ah\\@', 'from a derivative of \\\\2827\\\\', '', 'n f', 'company 1', 1, ' 1) a hut erected to pass the night in\r\n 2) a tent\r\n 3) anything to recline on\r\n    3a) a chair in which to lean back the head\r\n    3b) a reclining chair\r\n 4) a company reclining\r\n    4a) a row or party of persons reclining at meal\r\n'),
(2829, 'klope', '\\~kloph\\~ klope', '\\@klop-ay''\\@', 'from \\\\2813\\\\', '', 'n f', 'theft 2', 2, ' 1) theft\r\n'),
(2830, 'kludon', '\\~kludwn\\~ kludon', '\\@kloo''-dohn\\@', 'from kluzo (to billow or dash over)', '', 'n m', 'raging 1, wave 1', 2, ' 1) a dashing or surging wave, a surge, a violent agitation of the sea\r\n\r\n Sinonim   : Lihat Definisi \\\\5857\\\\\r\n'),
(2831, 'kludonizomai', '\\~kludwnizomai\\~ kludonizomai', '\\@kloo-do-nid''-zom-ahee\\@', 'middle voice from \\\\2830\\\\', '', 'v', 'toss to and fro 1', 1, ' 1) to be tossed by the waves\r\n 2) metaph. to be agitated (like the waves) mentally\r\n'),
(2832, 'Klopas', '\\~Klwpav\\~ Klopas', '\\@klo-pas''\\@', 'of Aramaic origin (corresponding to \\\\256\\\\)', '', 'n pr m', 'Cleophas 1', 1, ' Cleophas = "my exchanges"\r\n\r\n 1) the father of James the less, the husband of Mary the sister of\r\n    the mother of Jesus\r\n'),
(2833, 'knetho', '\\~knhyw\\~ knetho', '\\@knay''-tho\\@', 'from a primary knao (to scrape)', '', 'v', 'have itching 1', 1, ' 1) to scratch, tickle, make to itch\r\n 2) to itch\r\n 3) desirous of hearing something pleasant\r\n'),
(2834, 'Knidos', '\\~Knidov\\~ Knidos', '\\@knee''-dos\\@', 'probably of foreign origin', '', 'n pr loc', 'Cnidus 1', 1, ' Cnidus or Gnidus = "nettled"\r\n\r\n 1) a peninsula [now Cape Crio] and a city by the same name, situated\r\n    at the extreme south west of the peninsula of Asia Minor, on a\r\n    promontory now called Cape Crio, which projects between the\r\n    islands of Cos and Rhodes\r\n'),
(2835, 'kodrantes', '\\~kodranthv\\~ kodrantes', '\\@kod-ran''-tace\\@', 'of Latin origin', '', 'n m', 'farthing 2', 2, ' 1) a quadrans (about the fourth part of an "as"); in the NT a coin\r\n    equal to one half the Attic chalcus worth about 3/8 of a cent\r\n'),
(2836, 'koilia', '\\~koilia\\~ koilia', '\\@koy-lee''-ah\\@', 'from koilos ("hollow")', 'TDNT - 3:786,446', 'n f', 'womb 12, belly 11', 23, ' 1) the whole belly, the entire cavity\r\n    1a) the upper [i.e. stomach] and the lower belly are distinguished\r\n 2) the lower belly, the lower region, the receptacle of the excrement\r\n 3) the gullet\r\n    3a) to be given up to the pleasures of the palate, to gluttony\r\n 4) the womb, the place where the foetus is conceived and\r\n    nourished until birth\r\n    4a) of the uterus of animals\r\n 5) the innermost part of a man, the soul, heart as the seat of\r\n    thought, feeling, choice\r\n'),
(2837, 'koimao', '\\~koimaw\\~ koimao', '\\@koy-mah''-o\\@', 'from \\\\2749\\\\', '', 'v', 'sleep 10, fall asleep 4, be asleep 2, fall on sleep 1, be dead 1', 18, ' 1) to cause to sleep, put to sleep\r\n 2) metaph.\r\n    2a) to still, calm, quiet\r\n    2b) to fall asleep, to sleep\r\n    2c) to die\r\n'),
(2838, 'koimesis', '\\~koimhsiv\\~ koimesis', '\\@koy''-may-sis\\@', 'from \\\\2837\\\\', '', 'n f', 'taking of rest 1', 1, ' 1) a reposing, taking rest\r\n 2) a lying, reclining\r\n'),
