(2847, 'kokkinos', '\\~kokkinov\\~ kokkinos', '\\@kok''-kee-nos\\@', 'from \\\\2848\\\\ (from the kernel-shape of the insect)', 'TDNT - 3:812,450', 'adj', 'scarlet 4, scarlet colour 1, scarlet coloured 1', 6, ' 1) crimson, scarlet coloured. A kernel, the grain or berry of the\r\n    "ilex coccifera"; these berries are the clusters of the eggs of a\r\n    female insect, the "kermes" (resembling the cochineal), and when\r\n    collected and pulverised produces a red which was used in dyeing\r\n    (Pliny)\r\n 2) scarlet cloth or clothing\r\n'),
