(3446, 'morphosis', '\\~morfwsiv\\~ morphosis', '\\@mor''-fo-sis\\@', 'from \\\\3445\\\\', 'TDNT - 4:754,607', 'n f', 'form 2', 2, ' 1) a forming, shaping\r\n 2) form\r\n    2a) the mere form, semblance\r\n    2b) the form befitting a thing or truly expressing the fact,\r\n        the very form\r\n'),
