(4137, 'pleroo', '\\~plhrow\\~ pleroo', '\\@play-ro''-o\\@', 'from \\\\4134\\\\', 'TDNT - 6:286,867', 'v', 'fulfil 51, fill 19, be full 7, complete 2, end 2, misc 9', 90, ' 1) to make full, to fill up, i.e. to fill to the full\r\n    1a) to cause to abound, to furnish or supply liberally\r\n        1a1) I abound, I am liberally supplied\r\n 2) to render full, i.e. to complete\r\n   2a) to fill to the top: so that nothing shall be wanting to\r\n       full measure, fill to the brim\r\n   2b) to consummate: a number\r\n       2b1) to make complete in every particular, to render perfect\r\n       2b2) to carry through to the end, to accomplish, carry out,\r\n            (some undertaking)\r\n   2c) to carry into effect, bring to realisation, realise\r\n       2c1) of matters of duty: to perform, execute\r\n       2c2) of sayings, promises, prophecies, to bring to pass,\r\n            ratify, accomplish\r\n       2c3) to fulfil, i.e. to cause God''s will (as made known in the\r\n            law) to be obeyed as it should be, and God''s promises\r\n            (given through the prophets) to receive fulfilment\r\n'),
(4138, 'pleroma', '\\~plhrwma\\~ pleroma', '\\@play''-ro-mah\\@', 'from \\\\4137\\\\', 'TDNT - 6:298,867', 'n n', 'fulness 13, full 1, fulfilling 1, which is put in to fill up 1, pierce that filled up 1', 17, ' 1) that which is (has been) filled\r\n    1a) a ship inasmuch as it is filled (i.e. manned) with sailors,\r\n        rowers, and soldiers\r\n    1b) in the NT, the body of believers, as that which is filled with\r\n        the presence, power, agency, riches of God and of Christ\r\n 2) that which fills or with which a thing is filled\r\n    2a) of those things which a ship is filled, freight and\r\n        merchandise, sailors, oarsmen, soldiers\r\n    2b) completeness or fulness of time\r\n 3) fulness, abundance\r\n 4) a fulfilling, keeping\r\n'),
(4139, 'plesion', '\\~plhsion\\~ plesion', '\\@play-see''-on\\@', 'neuter of a derivative of pelas (near)', 'TDNT - 6:311,872', 'adv', 'neighbour 16, near 1', 17, ' 1) a neighbour\r\n    1a) a friend\r\n    1b) any other person, and where two are concerned, the other\r\n        (thy fellow man, thy neighbour), according to the Jews, any\r\n        member of the Hebrew nation and commonwealth\r\n    1c) according to Christ, any other man irrespective of nation or\r\n        religion with whom we live or whom we chance to meet\r\n'),
(4140, 'plesmone', '\\~plhsmonh\\~ plesmone', '\\@place-mon-ay''\\@', 'from a presumed derivative of \\\\4130\\\\', 'TDNT - 6:131,840', 'n f', 'satisfying 1', 1, ' 1) repletion, satiety, for the satisfying of the flesh, to\r\n    satiate the desires of the flesh\r\n    1a) indulgence of the flesh\r\n'),
(4141, 'plesso', '\\~plhssw\\~ plesso', '\\@place''-so\\@', 'apparently another form of \\\\4111\\\\ (through the idea of flattening out)', '', 'v', 'smite 1', 1, ' 1) to strike, smite\r\n'),
(4142, 'ploiarion', '\\~ploiarion\\~ ploiarion', '\\@ploy-ar''-ee-on\\@', 'from a presumed derivative of \\\\4143\\\\', '', 'n n', 'boat 3, little ship 2, small ship 1', 6, ' 1) a small vessel, a boat\r\n'),
(4143, 'ploion', '\\~ploion\\~ ploion', '\\@ploy''-on\\@', 'from \\\\4126\\\\', '', 'n n', 'ship 66, shipping 1', 67, ' 1) a ship\r\n'),
(4144, 'ploos', '\\~ploov\\~ ploos', '\\@plo''-os\\@', 'from \\\\4126\\\\', '', 'n m', 'course 1, sailing 1, voyage 1', 3, ' 1) a voyage\r\n'),
(4145, 'plousios', '\\~plousiov\\~ plousios', '\\@ploo''-see-os\\@', 'from \\\\4149\\\\', 'TDNT - 6:318,873', 'adj', 'rich 28', 28, ' 1) wealthy, abounding in material resources\r\n 2) metaph. abounding, abundantly supplied\r\n    2a) abounding (rich) in Christian virtues and eternal possessions\r\n'),
(4146, 'plousios', '\\~plousiwv\\~ plousios', '\\@ploo-see''-oce\\@', 'from \\\\4145\\\\', '', 'adv', 'richly 2, abundantly 2', 4, ' 1) abundantly, richly\r\n'),
(4147, 'plouteo', '\\~ploutew\\~ plouteo', '\\@ploo-teh''-o\\@', 'from \\\\4148\\\\', 'TDNT - 6:318,873', 'v', 'be rich 7, be made rich 2, rich 1, wax rich 1, be increased with goods 1', 12, ' 1) to be rich, to have abundance\r\n    1a) of outward possessions\r\n 2) metaph. to be richly supplied\r\n    2a) is affluent in resources so that he can give blessings of\r\n        salvation to all\r\n'),
(4148, 'ploutizo', '\\~ploutizw\\~ ploutizo', '\\@ploo-tid''-zo\\@', 'from \\\\4149\\\\', 'TDNT - 6:318,873', 'v', 'enrich 2, make rich 1', 3, ' 1) to make rich, enrich\r\n    1a) of spiritual riches\r\n 2) to be richly furnished\r\n'),
(4149, 'ploutos', '\\~ploutov\\~ ploutos', '\\@ploo''-tos\\@', 'from the base of \\\\4130\\\\', 'TDNT - 6:318,873', 'n m', 'riches 22', 22, ' 1) riches, wealth\r\n    1a) abundance of external possessions\r\n    1b) fulness, abundance, plenitude\r\n    1c) a good i.e. that with which one is enriched\r\n'),
(4150, 'pluno', '\\~plunw\\~ pluno', '\\@ploo''-no\\@', 'a prolonged form of an obsolete pluo (to "flow")', '', 'v', 'wash 1', 1, ' 1) to wash: with reference to clothing\r\n    1a) use figuratively of those who by faith so appropriate the\r\n        results of Christ''s expiation as to be regarded by God as\r\n        pure and sinless\r\n'),
(4151, 'pneuma', '\\~pneuma\\~ pneuma', '\\@pnyoo''-mah\\@', 'from \\\\4154\\\\', 'TDNT - 6:332,876', 'n n', 'Spirit 111, Holy Ghost 89, Spirit (of God) 13, Spirit (of the Lord) 5, (My) Spirit 3, Spirit (of truth) 3, Spirit (of Christ) 2, human (spirit) 49, (evil) spirit 47, spirit (general) 26, spirit 8, (Jesus'' own) spirit 6, (Jesus'' own) ghost 2, misc 21', 385, ' 1) the third person of the triune God, the Holy Spirit, coequal,\r\n    coeternal with the Father and the Son\r\n    1a) sometimes referred to in a way which emphasises his\r\n        personality and character (the \\\\Holy\\\\ Spirit)\r\n    1b) sometimes referred to in a way which emphasises his work\r\n        and power (the Spirit of \\\\Truth\\\\)\r\n    1c) never referred to as a depersonalised force\r\n 2) the spirit, i.e. the vital principal by which the body is animated\r\n    2a) the rational spirit, the power by which the human being feels,\r\n        thinks, decides\r\n    2b) the soul\r\n 3) a spirit, i.e. a simple essence, devoid of all or at least\r\n    all grosser matter, and possessed of the power of knowing,\r\n    desiring, deciding, and acting\r\n    3a) a life giving spirit\r\n    3b) a human soul that has left the body\r\n    3c) a spirit higher than man but lower than God, i.e. an angel\r\n        3c1) used of demons, or evil spirits, who were conceived\r\n             as inhabiting the bodies of men\r\n        3c2) the spiritual nature of Christ, higher than the highest\r\n             angels and equal to God, the divine nature of Christ\r\n 4) the disposition or influence which fills and governs the soul\r\n    of any one\r\n    4a) the efficient source of any power, affection, emotion, desire, etc.\r\n 5) a movement of air (a gentle blast)\r\n    5a) of the wind, hence the wind itself\r\n    5b) breath of nostrils or mouth\r\n\r\n Sinonim   : Lihat Definisi \\\\5923\\\\\r\n'),
(4152, 'pneumatikos', '\\~pneumatikov\\~ pneumatikos', '\\@pnyoo-mat-ik-os''\\@', 'from \\\\4151\\\\', 'TDNT - 6:332,876', 'adj', 'spiritual 26', 26, ' 1) relating to the human spirit, or rational soul, as part of the man\r\n    which is akin to God and serves as his instrument or organ\r\n    1a) that which possesses the nature of the rational soul\r\n 2) belonging to a spirit, or a being higher than man but inferior to God\r\n 3) belonging to the Divine Spirit\r\n    3a) of God the Holy Spirit\r\n    3b) one who is filled with and governed by the Spirit of God\r\n 4) pertaining to the wind or breath; windy, exposed to the wind, blowing\r\n'),
(4153, 'pneumatikos', '\\~pneumatikwv\\~ pneumatikos', '\\@pnyoo-mat-ik-oce''\\@', 'from \\\\4152\\\\', '', 'adv', 'spiritual 2', 2, ' 1) spiritually: i.e. by the aid of the Holy Spirit\r\n'),
(4154, 'pneo', '\\~pnew\\~ pneo', '\\@pneh''-o\\@', 'a root word', 'TDNT - 6:452,876', 'v', 'blow 6, wind 1', 7, ' 1) to breathe, to blow\r\n    1a) of the wind\r\n'),
(4155, 'pnigo', '\\~pnigw\\~ pnigo', '\\@pnee''-go\\@', 'strengthened from \\\\4154\\\\', 'TDNT - 6:455,895', 'v', 'take by the throat 1, choke 1', 2, ' 1) to choke, strangle\r\n    1a) of thorns crowding out the seed in the field and hindering\r\n        its growth\r\n 2) to wring one''s neck, throttle\r\n'),
(4156, 'pniktos', '\\~pniktov\\~ pniktos', '\\@pnik-tos''\\@', 'from \\\\4155\\\\', 'TDNT - 6:455,895', 'adj', 'strangled 3', 3, ' 1) suffocate, strangled\r\n    1a) what is strangled, i.e. an animal deprived of life without\r\n        the shedding of blood\r\n    1b) of cooking: our "smothered" as a culinary term\r\n'),
(4157, 'pnoe', '\\~pnoh\\~ pnoe', '\\@pno-ay''\\@', 'from \\\\4154\\\\', 'TDNT - 6:453,876', 'n f', 'wind 1, breath 1', 2, ' 1) breath, breath of life\r\n 2) wind\r\n\r\n Sinonim   : Lihat Definisi \\\\5923\\\\\r\n'),
(4158, 'poderes', '\\~podhrhv\\~ poderes', '\\@pod-ay''-race\\@', 'from \\\\4228\\\\ and another element of uncertain affinity', '', 'adj', 'garment down to the foot 1', 1, ' 1) reaching to the feet\r\n 2) a garment reaching to the ankles, coming down to the feet\r\n\r\n Sinonim   : Lihat Definisi \\\\5934\\\\\r\n'),
(4159, 'pothen', '\\~poyen\\~ pothen', '\\@poth''-en\\@', 'from the base of \\\\4213\\\\ with enclitic adverb of origin', '', 'adv', 'whence 28', 28, ' 1) of place: from where, from what condition\r\n 2) of origin or source: from what author or giver\r\n 3) of cause: how is that?, how can that be?\r\n'),
(4160, 'poieo', '\\~poiew\\~ poieo', '\\@poy-eh''-o\\@', 'apparently a prolonged form of an obsolete primary', 'TDNT - 6:458,895', 'v', 'do 357, make 113, bring forth 14, commit 9, cause 9, work 8, show 5, bear 4, keep 4, fulfil 3, deal 2, perform 2, not tr 3, misc 43, vr do 3', 579, ' 1) to make\r\n    1a) with the names of things made, to produce, construct,\r\n        form, fashion, etc.\r\n    1b) to be the authors of, the cause\r\n    1c) to make ready, to prepare\r\n    1d) to produce, bear, shoot forth\r\n    1e) to acquire, to provide a thing for one''s self\r\n    1f) to make a thing out of something\r\n    1g) to (make i.e.) render one anything\r\n        1g1) to (make i.e.) constitute or appoint one anything, to\r\n             appoint or ordain one that\r\n        1g2) to (make i.e.) declare one anything\r\n    1h) to put one forth, to lead him out\r\n    1i) to make one do something\r\n        1i1) cause one to\r\n    1j) to be the authors of a thing (to cause, bring about)\r\n 2) to do\r\n    2a) to act rightly, do well\r\n        2a1) to carry out, to execute\r\n    2b) to do a thing unto one\r\n        2b1) to do to one\r\n    2c) with designation of time: to pass, spend\r\n    2d) to celebrate, keep\r\n        2d1) to make ready, and so at the same time to institute,\r\n             the celebration of the passover\r\n    2e) to perform: to a promise\r\n\r\n Sinonim   : Lihat Definisi \\\\5871\\\\\r\n                        dan \\\\5911\\\\\r\n'),
(4161, 'poiema', '\\~poihma\\~ poiema', '\\@poy''-ay-mah\\@', 'from \\\\4160\\\\', 'TDNT - 6:458,895', 'n n', 'thing that is made 1, workmanship 1', 2, ' 1) that which has been made\r\n 2) a work\r\n    2a) of the works of God as creator\r\n'),
(4162, 'poiesis', '\\~poihsiv\\~ poiesis', '\\@poy''-ay-sis\\@', 'from \\\\4160\\\\', 'TDNT - 6:458,895', 'n f', 'deed 1', 1, ' 1) a making\r\n 2) a doing or performing\r\n    2a) in his doing i.e. in the obedience he renders to the law\r\n'),
(4163, 'poietes', '\\~poihthv\\~ poietes', '\\@poy-ay-tace''\\@', 'from \\\\4160\\\\', 'TDNT - 6:458,895', 'n m', 'doer 5, poet 1', 6, ' 1) a maker, a producer, author\r\n 2) a doer, performer\r\n    2a) one who obeys or fulfils the law\r\n 3) a poet\r\n'),
(4164, 'poikilos', '\\~poikilov\\~ poikilos', '\\@poy-kee''-los\\@', 'of uncertain derivation', 'TDNT - 6:484,901', 'adj', 'divers 8, manifold 2', 10, ' 1) a various colours, variegated\r\n 2) of various sorts\r\n'),
(4165, 'poimaino', '\\~poimainw\\~ poimaino', '\\@poy-mah''-ee-no\\@', 'from \\\\4166\\\\', 'TDNT - 6:485,901', 'v', 'feed 6, rule 4, feed cattle 1', 11, ' 1) to feed, to tend a flock, keep sheep\r\n   1a) to rule, govern\r\n      1a1) of rulers\r\n      1a2) to furnish pasture for food\r\n      1a3) to nourish\r\n      1a4) to cherish one''s body, to serve the body\r\n      1a5) to supply the requisites for the soul''s need\r\n\r\n Sinonim   : Lihat Definisi \\\\5824\\\\\r\n'),
(4166, 'poimen', '\\~poimhn\\~ poimen', '\\@poy-mane''\\@', 'of uncertain affinity', 'TDNT - 6:485,901', 'n m', 'shepherd 15, Shepherd 2, pastor 1', 18, ' 1) a herdsman, esp. a shepherd\r\n    1a) in the parable, he to whose care and control others have\r\n        committed themselves, and whose precepts they follow\r\n 2) metaph.\r\n    2a) the presiding officer, manager, director, of any assembly:\r\n        so of Christ the Head of the church\r\n        2a1) of the overseers of the Christian assemblies\r\n        2a2) of kings and princes\r\n ++++\r\n The tasks of a Near Eastern shepherd were:\r\n    - to watch for enemies trying to attack the sheep\r\n    - to defend the sheep from attackers\r\n    - to heal the wounded and sick sheep\r\n    - to find and save lost or trapped sheep\r\n    - to love them, sharing their lives and so earning their trust.\r\n\r\n During World War II, a shepherd was a pilot who guided another pilot\r\n whose plane was partially disabled back to the base or carrier by\r\n flying alongside him to maintain visual contact.\r\n'),
(4167, 'poimne', '\\~poimnh\\~ poimne', '\\@poym''-nay\\@', 'contraction from \\\\4165\\\\', 'TDNT - 6:499,901', 'n f', 'flock 4, fold 1', 5, ' 1) a flock (esp.) of sheep\r\n    1a) of Christ''s flock i.e. the body of those who follow Jesus as\r\n        their guide and keeper\r\n'),
(4168, 'poimnion', '\\~poimnion\\~ poimnion', '\\@poym''-nee-on\\@', 'neuter of a presumed derivative of \\\\4167\\\\', 'TDNT - 6:499,901', 'n n', 'flock 5', 5, ' 1) a flock (esp.) of sheep\r\n 2) a group of Christ''s disciples\r\n 3) bodies of Christian (churches) presided over by elders\r\n'),
(4169, 'poios', '\\~poiov\\~ poios', '\\@poy''-os\\@', 'from the base of \\\\4226\\\\ and \\\\3634\\\\', '', 'pron', 'what 27, which 4, what things 1, what way 1, what manner of 1', 34, ' 1) of what sort or nature\r\n'),
(4170, 'polemeo', '\\~polemew\\~ polemeo', '\\@pol-em-eh''-o\\@', 'from \\\\4171\\\\', 'TDNT - 6:502,904', 'v', 'make war 3, fight 3, war 1', 7, ' 1) to war, carry on war\r\n 2) to fight\r\n'),
(4171, 'polemos', '\\~polemov\\~ polemos', '\\@pol''-em-os\\@', 'from pelomai (to bustle)', 'TDNT - 6:502,904', 'n m', 'war 12, battle 5, fight 1', 18, ' 1) a war\r\n 2) a fight, a battle\r\n 3) a dispute, strife, quarrel\r\n\r\n Sinonim   : Lihat Definisi \\\\5938\\\\\r\n'),
(4172, 'polis', '\\~poliv\\~ polis', '\\@pol''-is\\@', 'probably from the same as \\\\4171\\\\, or perhaps from \\\\4183\\\\', 'TDNT - 6:516,906', 'n f', 'city 164', 164, ' 1) a city\r\n    1a) one''s native city, the city in which one lives\r\n    1b) the heavenly Jerusalem\r\n        1b1) the abode of the blessed in heaven\r\n        1b2) of the visible capital in the heavenly kingdom, to come\r\n             down to earth after the renovation of the world by fire\r\n    1c) the inhabitants of a city\r\n'),
(4173, 'politarches', '\\~politarchv\\~ politarches', '\\@pol-it-ar''-khace\\@', 'from \\\\4172\\\\ and \\\\757\\\\', '', 'n m', 'ruler of the city 2', 2, ' 1) a ruler of a city or citizens\r\n'),
(4174, 'politeia', '\\~politeia\\~ politeia', '\\@pol-ee-ti''-ah\\@', 'from \\\\4177\\\\ ("polity")', 'TDNT - 6:516,906', 'n f', 'freedom 1, commonwealth 1', 2, ' 1) the administration of civil affairs\r\n 2) a state or commonwealth\r\n 3) citizenship, the rights of a citizen\r\n'),
(4175, 'politeuma', '\\~politeuma\\~ politeuma', '\\@pol-it''-yoo-mah\\@', 'from \\\\4176\\\\', 'TDNT - 6:516,906', 'n n', 'conversation 1', 1, ' 1) the administration of civil affairs or of a commonwealth\r\n 2) the constitution of a commonwealth, form of government and\r\n    the laws by which it is administered\r\n 3) a state, commonwealth\r\n    3a) the commonwealth of citizens\r\n');
INSERT INTO `greek` (`id`, `word_id`, `word`, `pron`, `origin`, `source`, `kind`, `av`, `count`, `definition`) VALUES
(4176, 'politeuomai', '\\~politeuomai\\~ politeuomai', '\\@pol-it-yoo''-om-ahee\\@', 'middle voice of a derivative of \\\\4177\\\\', 'TDNT - 6:516,906', 'v', 'live 1, let (one''s) conversation be 1', 2, ' 1) to be a citizen\r\n 2) to administer civil affairs, manage the state\r\n 3) to make or create a citizen\r\n    3a) to be a citizen\r\n    3b) to behave as a citizen\r\n        3b1) to avail one''s self of or recognise the laws\r\n        3b2) to conduct one''s self as pledged to some law of life\r\n'),
(4177, 'polites', '\\~polithv\\~ polites', '\\@pol-ee''-tace\\@', 'from \\\\4172\\\\', 'TDNT - 6:516,906', 'n m', 'citizen 3', 3, ' 1) a citizen\r\n    1a) the inhabitant of any city or country\r\n    1b) the association of another in citizenship\r\n        1b1) a fellow citizen, fellow countryman\r\n'),
(4178, 'pollakis', '\\~pollakiv\\~ pollakis', '\\@pol-lak''-is\\@', 'multiplicative adverb from \\\\4183\\\\', '', 'adv', 'often 7, oft 5, ofttimes 3, oftentimes 3', 18, ' 1) often, frequently\r\n'),
(4179, 'pollaplasion', '\\~pollaplasiwn\\~ pollaplasion', '\\@pol-lap-las-ee''-ohn\\@', 'from \\\\4183\\\\ and probably a derivative of \\\\4120\\\\', '', 'adv', 'manifold more 1', 1, ' 1) manifold, much, more\r\n'),
(4180, 'polulogia', '\\~polulogia\\~ polulogia', '\\@pol-oo-log-ee''-ah\\@', 'from a compound of \\\\4183\\\\ and \\\\3056\\\\', 'TDNT - 6:545,911', 'n f', 'much speaking 1', 1, ' 1) much speaking\r\n'),
(4181, 'polumeros', '\\~polumerwv\\~ polumeros', '\\@pol-oo-mer''-oce\\@', 'from a compound of \\\\4183\\\\ and \\\\3313\\\\', '', 'adv', 'at sundry times 1', 1, ' 1) by many portions, by many times and in many ways\r\n'),
(4182, 'polupoikilos', '\\~polupoikilov\\~ polupoikilos', '\\@pol-oo-poy''-kil-os\\@', 'from \\\\4183\\\\ and \\\\4164\\\\', 'TDNT - 6:485,901', 'adj', 'manifold 1', 1, ' 1) much variegated, marked with a great variety of colours\r\n    1a1) of cloth or a painting\r\n 2) much varied, manifold\r\n'),
(4183, 'polus', '\\~poluv\\~ polus', '\\@pol-oos''\\@', 'including the forms from the alternate pollos', 'TDNT - 6:536,*', 'adj', 'many 210, much 73, great 59, misc 23', 365, ' 1) many, much, large\r\n'),
(4184, 'polusplagchnos', '\\~polusplagchov\\~ polusplagchnos', '\\@pol-oo''-splankh-nos\\@', 'from \\\\4183\\\\ and \\\\4698\\\\ (figuratively)', 'TDNT - 7:548,1067', 'adj', 'very pitiful 1', 1, ' 1) full of pity, very kind\r\n'),
(4185, 'poluteles', '\\~polutelhv\\~ poluteles', '\\@pol-oo-tel-ace''\\@', 'from \\\\4183\\\\ and \\\\5056\\\\', '', 'adj', 'very precious 1, costly 1, of great price 1', 3, ' 1) precious\r\n    1a) requiring very great outlay, very costly\r\n    1b) excellent, of surpassing value\r\n'),
(4186, 'polutimos', '\\~polutimov\\~ polutimos', '\\@pol-oot''-ee-mos\\@', 'from \\\\4183\\\\ and \\\\5092\\\\', '', 'adj', 'of great price 1, very costly 1', 2, ' 1) very valuable, of great price\r\n'),
(4187, 'polutropos', '\\~polutropwv\\~ polutropos', '\\@pol-oot-rop''-oce\\@', 'from a compound of \\\\4183\\\\ and \\\\5158\\\\', '', 'adv', 'in divers manners 1', 1, ' 1) in many manners\r\n'),
(4188, 'poma', '\\~poma\\~ poma', '\\@pom''-ah\\@', 'from the alternate of \\\\4095\\\\', 'TDNT - 6:145,840', 'n n', 'drink 2', 2, ' 1) drink\r\n'),
(4189, 'poneria', '\\~ponhria\\~ poneria', '\\@pon-ay-ree''-ah\\@', 'from \\\\4190\\\\', 'TDNT - 6:562,912', 'n f', 'wickedness 6, iniquity 1', 7, ' 1) depravity, iniquity, wickedness\r\n 2) malice\r\n 3) evil purposes and desires\r\n\r\n Sinonim   : Lihat Definisi \\\\5855\\\\\r\n'),
(4190, 'poneros', '\\~ponhrov\\~ poneros', '\\@pon-ay-ros''\\@', 'from a derivative of \\\\4192\\\\', 'TDNT - 6:546,912', 'adj', 'evil 51, wicked 10, wicked one 6, evil things 2, misc 7', 76, ' 1) full of labours, annoyances, hardships\r\n    1a) pressed and harassed by labours\r\n    1b) bringing toils, annoyances, perils; of a time full of\r\n        peril to Christian faith and steadfastness; causing pain and\r\n        trouble\r\n 2) bad, of a bad nature or condition\r\n    2a) in a physical sense: diseased or blind\r\n    2b) in an ethical sense: evil wicked, bad\r\n\r\n Sinonim   : Lihat Definisi \\\\5908\\\\\r\n ++++\r\n The word is used in the nominative case in \\\\#Mt 6:13\\\\. This usually\r\n denotes a title in the Greek. Hence Christ is saying, deliver us\r\n from "The Evil", and is probably referring to Satan.\r\n'),
